{# 
  =============================================================================
  COMPONENT: Lead Story Grid (Institutional Front-End)
  STABILITY: Production-Stable / Architecture: Sinn 556 iRS Equivalent
  VERSION: 2.1.0 (Drupal 11 / PHP 8.4 Optimized)
  COMPLIANCE: Section 508 / WCAG 2.2 Level AA / ADA Title II Ready
  =============================================================================
  ARCHITECTURAL DESIGN RATIONALE:
  - Utilizes a "Block-Link" UX Pattern: The entire card is encapsulated within 
    a semantic <a> tag to maximize the "hit area" for mobile/touch users.
  - Heading Hierarchy: Employs a dual-layer heading strategy to satisfy SEO 
    requirements while providing high-fidelity navigation for AT (Assistive Tech).
  - Flexbox Distribution: Implements a nested Flexbox model to ensure 
    consistent card heights and footer alignment regardless of content delta.

  ACCESSIBILITY NOTES:
  - Aria-Label: Specifically curated to provide action context without 
    verbosity (e.g., omitting "click here" or "link").
  - Role Assignment: Uses 'list' and 'listitem' roles to compensate for 
    non-standard <div> based grid layouts in legacy screen readers.
  =============================================================================

  OVERVIEW
  --------
  This template renders a responsive 4-column grid of "Lead Story" impact cards
  used to showcase donor impact narratives across CU's campuses. Unlike the
  Give Now grid (block--give-now.html.twig) which drives donation actions, this
  component is editorial — it surfaces stories that motivate giving rather than
  soliciting it directly.

  The component is paired with a "Browse More Stories" global CTA footer that
  routes to /impact-stories, making this grid the entry point of a larger
  stories ecosystem.

  CONTENT TYPE
  ------------
  Cards are sourced from Drupal nodes. Despite the admin link pointing to
  /node/add/gi, confirm the actual machine name of the content type with the
  site's content model documentation — it may share the "gi" type with Give Now
  items, distinguished by a field or bundle, or it may be a separate type.
  Clarify this before adding any preprocess logic.

  SISTER TEMPLATE
  ---------------
  This component shares significant structural DNA with block--give-now.html.twig
  (v2.2.0). Key differences to be aware of:
    1. Grid element: Uses <div role="list"> + <div role="listitem"> instead of
       semantic <ul>/<li>. See the ROLE ASSIGNMENT section below for rationale.
    2. Heading pattern: Uses a visually-hidden <h4> + aria-hidden <p> instead
       of the Give Now pattern of aria-hidden <h4> alone.
    3. The section <h3> here is VISIBLE (cua-gold text-center) vs. visually
       hidden in Give Now. Different editorial intent — this heading is a marketing statement, not just an accessibility anchor.
    4. Missing: field_shadow toggle. Shadow is applied unconditionally here
       via the hard-coded 'shadow' class on <article>.
    5. Extra: Global CTA footer (Browse More Stories) after the loop — absent
       in Give Now.
    6. Missing: The id attribute on the <a> card anchor present in Give Now.
       If per-card anchor deep-linking is ever needed, this will need adding.

  WHERE THIS TEMPLATE LIVES IN THE THEME
  ---------------------------------------
  Expected path (relative to theme root):
    templates/block/block--lead-story.html.twig
  OR as a Views block override:
    templates/views/views-view--lead-stories.html.twig
  Verify the active suggestion in the Twig debug comments in the page source
  (enable twig.config.debug in services.yml locally to inspect).

  BLOCK / PLUGIN VARIABLES AVAILABLE IN SCOPE
  --------------------------------------------
  - configuration  : Block plugin configuration array. Provides
                     configuration.provider for CSS class generation
                     (e.g., "block_content", "views").
  - plugin_id      : Machine name of the block plugin
                     (e.g., "views_block:lead_stories-block_1").
                     Used for BEM-style CSS scoping.
  - id             : Block placement instance ID. May be null in non-block
                     render contexts (Layout Builder preview, sort page).
                     Always guarded with ?: fallback.
  - utility_classes: Array of extra CSS classes injected by Layout Builder
                     or preprocess hooks. Merged into givenow_classes.
                     Note: variable is named givenow_classes here — see CSS
                     CLASS ASSEMBLY note below about the naming inconsistency.
  - content        : Standard Drupal block render array.
                     content['#view'] holds the Views object.
  - user           : Current Drupal user object for permission checks.
  - title_prefix / title_suffix : Drupal contextual link wrappers. Must
                     always be present. See individual notes below.
#}

{#
  LIBRARY ATTACHMENT
  ------------------
  Attaches 'call-to-action' JS/CSS library from cua_theme.libraries.yml.
  This is the same library used by block--give-now.html.twig. It is expected
  to provide:
    - Hover/transition effects for .story-link anchors
    - Click-tracking / analytics event wiring for data-story-* attributes
    - Any entrance animation or lazy-reveal JS behavior

  If you see missing styles or broken hover states, check that this library
  is defined and that its asset paths resolve correctly. Drupal will log a
  warning (not an error) if the library is missing, so cards will still
  render without it.
#}
{{ attach_library('cua_theme/call-to-action') }}

{# 
  DYNAMIC CLASS ORCHESTRATION:
  We merge Drupal-provided utility classes with hard-coded component classes 
  to maintain a strictly decoupled layout system. 

  DEV NOTE — CSS CLASS ASSEMBLY (givenow_classes)
  ------------------------------------------------
  ⚠ NAMING INCONSISTENCY: This variable is named `givenow_classes` but this
  is the Lead Story template, not Give Now. This is a copy-paste artifact from
  the sister template and should be renamed `lead_story_classes` in a future
  refactor. It is functionally correct — the name has no runtime effect — but
  it creates confusion when reading the markup below where the same variable
  name appears on the card anchor.

  Class breakdown:
    'block'
      → Standard Drupal block wrapper class. Expected by base theme styles.
    'block-' ~ configuration.provider|clean_class
      → Provider-scoped class, e.g. "block-block-content".
        clean_class normalizes unsafe characters (spaces → hyphens).
    'block-' ~ plugin_id|clean_class
      → Plugin-scoped class, e.g. "block-views-block-lead-stories-block-1".
    'col'
      → Bootstrap 5 column base class required for grid children.
    'lead-story-item'
      → Component-specific hook for CSS and JS targeting. Note: differs
        from Give Now's 'give-now-item'. Make sure _lead-story.scss targets
        this class and not the Give Now one.
    id ? 'block--class--lead-story-' ~ id|clean_class : null
      → Optional unique class per block placement for per-instance CSS
        overrides. Safely returns null when id is absent.
    merge(utility_classes ?: [])
      → Appends Layout Builder or preprocess-injected utility classes.
        ?: [] guards against undefined variable crash.
    | filter(v => v)
      → Strips nulls and empty strings from the array.
    | join(' ')
      → Collapses to a single space-separated class string.

  IMPORTANT: Do NOT add responsive column classes (col-12, col-sm-6, col-lg-3)
  here. They belong on the <div role="listitem"> wrapper, not the <a> element.
#}
{% set givenow_classes = [
    'block',
    'block-' ~ configuration.provider|clean_class,
    'block-' ~ plugin_id|clean_class,
    'col',
    'lead-story-item',
    id ? 'block--class--lead-story-' ~ id|clean_class : null,
] | merge(utility_classes ?: []) | filter(v => v) | join(' ') %}

{# 
  ADMINISTRATIVE CONTROL LAYER:
  Conditional rendering of management hooks for content editors.
  Restricted to users with 'administer site configuration' permissions.

  DEV NOTE — ADMIN TOOLBAR
  ------------------------
  Two quick-links are provided:
    /lead-story/sort  → The drag-and-drop sort/weight management page for
                        ordering story cards. This is likely a custom Views
                        page or a contrib module (e.g., Weight, Draggableviews).
                        If this URL 404s in a new environment, check that the
                        relevant module is enabled and the route is registered.
    /node/add/gi      → Add a new node. Confirm content type machine name
                        matches "gi" — see CONTENT TYPE note in the header.

  role="group" + aria-label="Editor Shortcuts" groups the admin links for
  AT users who have admin permissions. Invisible to public users entirely.
  Bootstrap 5 utilities (d-flex, justify-content-center, m-2, mx-2) handle
  the horizontal layout.
#}
{% if user.hasPermission('administer site configuration') %}
    <div class="admin-interface d-flex justify-content-center m-2" role="group" aria-label="Editor Shortcuts">
        <a href="/lead-story/sort" class="btn btn-secondary mx-2">{{ 'Sort and manage lead stories'|t }}</a>
        <a href="/node/add/gi" class="btn btn-secondary mx-2">{{ 'Add new lead story'|t }}</a>
    </div>
{% endif %}

{# 
  DEV NOTE: CONTEXTUAL LINKS
  `title_prefix` and `title_suffix` are required by Drupal's Render API.
  If these are removed, the quick-edit "pencil" icon will not appear for content editors when hovering over this block.
#}
{{ title_prefix }}
{{ title_suffix }}

{# 
  DATA VALIDATION & LOOP INITIALIZATION:
  Ensures the 'view' object exists and contains valid results before 
  committing to DOM rendering, protecting against empty-state bloat.

  DEV NOTE — GUARD CHAIN
  -----------------------
  Two nested guards protect against two distinct failure modes:

  1. content['#view'] is not empty
     → The outer guard. content['#view'] is only populated when this block
       wraps a Drupal View. In Layout Builder preview, Drush exports, or the
       sort/admin page, this key may be absent entirely. `is not empty`
       preferred over `is defined` because an initialized-but-empty Views
       object should also be skipped.

  2. view.result is not empty
     → The inner guard. Protects against a View that exists but returned
       zero rows (no published stories, all filtered out by exposed filters,
       or contextual filter with no match). An empty result renders nothing —
       no container, no heading — rather than an empty gray shell.
       This is intentional UX; if you need an empty-state message, add it
       in an {% else %} block here.
#}
{% if content['#view'] is not empty %}
    {% set view = content['#view'] %}
    {% if view.result is not empty %}

        {#
          OUTER CONTAINER
          ---------------
          Full-bleed fluid container. Class breakdown:
            container-fluid       → removes max-width cap, edge-to-edge layout
            cu-bd-black           → CUA custom class; likely sets a black or
                                    very dark background. Check _colors.scss.
            pt-3                  → top padding (tighter than Give Now's pt-1)
            pb-5                  → generous bottom padding for section separation
            px-2                  → horizontal gutter to prevent cards touching
                                    the viewport edge on mobile
        #}
        <div class="container-fluid cu-bd-black pt-3 pb-5 px-2">

            {#
              SECTION HEADING — VISIBLE MARKETING STATEMENT
              -----------------------------------------------
              Unlike the Give Now grid where the equivalent <h3> is
              visually-hidden (accessibility anchor only), this heading is
              VISIBLE and styled as a marketing tagline.

              id="lead-story-section-title" → referenced by the grid
                container's aria-labelledby below (WCAG 1.3.1).
              cua-gold → CUA theme custom color utility. Renders the heading
                in CU gold against the dark cu-bd-black background.
              text-center mb-4 → centered layout with bottom margin.

              COPY NOTE: "How Giving Shapes Lives at Colorado's University
              Campuses" uses the |t filter for Drupal's translation system.
              If this needs to be editable by content admins (not just
              translators), consider moving it to a block field rather than
              hardcoding it in the template.
            #}
            <h3 id="lead-story-section-title" class="cua-gold text-center mb-4">
                {{ "How Giving Shapes Lives at Colorado's University Campuses"|t }}
            </h3>

            {#
              GRID CONTAINER — DIV-BASED LIST WITH ARIA ROLES
              ------------------------------------------------
              DEV NOTE — WHY <div role="list"> INSTEAD OF <ul>?
              This is the key structural difference from block--give-now.html.twig
              which uses a semantic <ul>/<li> grid. Here, <div> with explicit
              role="list" + role="listitem" is used instead.

              The rationale (per the header's ACCESSIBILITY NOTES):
                Some legacy screen readers (notably older VoiceOver + Safari
                combinations) strip list semantics from <ul> elements when
                CSS resets apply `list-style: none`. The Bootstrap `list-unstyled`
                class triggers this in some environments. Using explicit ARIA
                roles on <div> elements sidesteps the CSS-stripping issue
                entirely and guarantees list semantics across all AT.

              WCAG NOTE: role="list" on a <div> combined with
              aria-labelledby="lead-story-section-title" satisfies WCAG 1.3.1
              (Info and Relationships) — the list has a programmatic label
              pointing to the visible <h3> above.

              Bootstrap classes:
                'row' → flex row container for the Bootstrap 5 grid.
            #}
            <div class="row" role="list" aria-labelledby="lead-story-section-title">

                {#
                  ROW LOOP — ViewsResultRow iteration
                  -------------------------------------
                  Each `row` is a ViewsResultRow object from the Views result set.
                  The entity itself is accessed via row._entity (underscore prefix
                  = Views internal property, not a public field).

                  The `row._entity is not empty` guard is critical:
                    - Prevents a crash if the node was deleted after the View's
                      query ran (race condition between query and render).
                    - Prevents errors if a Views relationship returned no entity
                      (e.g., a missing translation in multilingual setups).
                    - Protects against the sort page context where _entity may
                      be partially hydrated.
                #}
                {% for row in view.result %}
                    {% if row._entity is not empty %}
                        
                        {# 
                          ENTITY MAPPING:
                          Extracting node-level data early to clean up the markup below.

                          DEV NOTE — LOCAL VARIABLE SETUP
                          --------------------------------
                          node       : The story content entity. All field access flows
                                       through this variable. Field names follow the Drupal
                                       field machine name convention (field_*).
                          heading_id : Unique DOM ID for the visible <p> title element.
                                       Scoped to node.id to guarantee uniqueness on the
                                       page even if multiple instances of this block are
                                       placed in the same layout. Used as a potential
                                       aria-labelledby target for future refactors.
                          link       : Resolved URI from field_link. The ?: '#' fallback
                                       prevents a broken or absent href when the editor
                                       hasn't configured a URL. In production, a '#' link
                                       means the node is missing its destination — consider
                                       logging a watchdog warning in a preprocess hook if
                                       link evaluates to '#'.

                          NOTE: Unlike the Give Now template, there is no `body_id` variable
                          here because this template does not use aria-describedby on the
                          card anchor. If you add it in a future accessibility pass, follow
                          the Give Now pattern: set body_id and add aria-describedby="{{ body_id }}"
                          to the <a> element.
                        #}
                        {% set node = row._entity %}
                        {% set heading_id = 'lead-story-item-' ~ node.id ~ '-title' %}
                        {% set link = node.field_link.uri ?: '#' %}

                        {#
                          GRID COLUMN WRAPPER — <div role="listitem">
                          --------------------------------------------
                          Responsive column classes:
                            col-12    → full width on xs (mobile, <576px)
                            col-sm-6  → 2-column layout on small (≥576px)
                            col-lg-3  → 4-column layout on large (≥992px)
                          lead-story-wrapper → component CSS/JS hook
                          mb-4               → bottom margin to separate rows
                          role="listitem"    → pairs with role="list" on parent
                                              <div> — see GRID CONTAINER note above
                        #}
                        <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-lg-3 lead-story-wrapper mb-4" role="listitem">

                            {# 
                              SEMANTIC ANCHOR — FULL-CARD CLICKABLE LINK
                              -------------------------------------------
                              The entire card is wrapped in a single <a> to create
                              a large touch target on mobile (the "card link" pattern).

                              ACCESSIBILITY DECISIONS:
                                aria-label="Read story: {node.label}"
                                  → Provides an action-oriented label for screen
                                    readers. "Read story:" is a deliberate prefix
                                    that distinguishes these from the Give Now links
                                    ("Give now to:") so AT users navigating a page
                                    that contains both grids can tell them apart.
                                  → Does NOT use aria-describedby (unlike Give Now).
                                    If body text is important for AT context, add
                                    a body_id variable and aria-describedby in a
                                    future pass.

                              NOTE: There is NO id attribute on this <a>, unlike the
                              Give Now card anchor (id="give-now-item-{{ node.id }}").
                              If per-card deep-linking or JS targeting by ID is
                              needed in the future, add id="lead-story-item-{{ node.id }}".

                              DATA ATTRIBUTES (consumed by call-to-action JS library):
                                data-story-id    → Node ID for analytics event tracking
                                data-story-title → Node title for GA event label
                                                   |e('html_attr') escapes quotes/special
                                                   chars for safe attribute embedding
                                data-story-url   → Destination URL for deferred navigation
                                data-block-id    → Block placement ID; falls back to
                                                   'lead-stories' string when id is null
                                                   (e.g., sort page, Layout Builder preview)

                              LAYOUT CLASSES:
                                text-decoration-none → removes underline from link
                                h-100               → stretches to full <div> height
                                                      enabling equal-height cards in a row
                                d-flex flex-column  → enables the sticky-footer pattern
                                                      for the CTA button at card bottom
                                story-link          → JS hook for the CTA library
                            #}
                            <a href="{{ link }}"
                               class="{{ givenow_classes }} text-decoration-none h-100 d-flex flex-column story-link"
                               aria-label="Read story: {{ node.label }}"
                               data-story-id="{{ node.id }}"
                               data-story-title="{{ node.label|e('html_attr') }}"
                               data-story-url="{{ link }}"
                               data-block-id="{{ id ?: 'lead-stories' }}">

                                {#
                                  CARD ARTICLE
                                  ------------
                                  <article> is semantically appropriate — each card
                                  represents a self-contained story that could stand
                                  alone if syndicated or extracted from context.

                                  Class breakdown:
                                    m-2     → outer margin creating a gutter between
                                              cards within the same Bootstrap column
                                    shadow  → Bootstrap drop shadow. Applied
                                              UNCONDITIONALLY here, unlike Give Now
                                              which uses a per-node field_shadow toggle.
                                              If per-card shadow control is needed,
                                              add field_shadow to the content type and
                                              apply the same conditional used in Give Now.
                                    node.field_color_background.value ?: 'cua-black-opacity-75'
                                              → Editor-selected background color class
                                                (e.g., "bg-gold", "bg-dark-blue") OR the
                                                default 'cua-black-opacity-75' if empty.
                                                Note the fallback value — unlike Give Now
                                                which falls back to no class, this always
                                                applies a background. Check _colors.scss
                                                for 'cua-black-opacity-75' definition.
                                    flex-grow-1 d-flex flex-column
                                              → Enables content to fill the full height
                                                of the <a> wrapper, and allows the CTA
                                                footer to stick to the bottom via
                                                `mt-auto` or margin on the footer div.
                                #}
                                <article class="m-2 shadow {{ node.field_color_background.value ?: 'cua-black-opacity-75' }} flex-grow-1 d-flex flex-column">

                                    {#
                                      DUAL HEADING STRATEGY — LAYER 1 (SCREEN READER ONLY)
                                      -----------------------------------------------------
                                      This visually-hidden <h4> exists to satisfy two goals:
                                        1. SEO: Provides a heading in the document outline
                                           that search crawlers can follow.
                                        2. AT Navigation: Users of screen readers who
                                           navigate by headings (H key in NVDA/JAWS) will
                                           land on this heading and hear the story title,
                                           giving them context before they choose to enter
                                           the link.

                                      The |t filter on the concatenated string is intentional
                                      for i18n — "Read more about" is a translatable prefix.

                                      ⚠ ARIA INTERACTION WARNING:
                                      This heading is inside the <a> card link. Nesting a
                                      heading inside an <a> is technically valid HTML5 (block
                                      elements can appear in <a> in HTML5), but some screen
                                      readers may announce both the heading AND the link label.
                                      Test with NVDA + Chrome and VoiceOver + Safari if you
                                      receive bug reports about double-reading of story titles.
                                      The Give Now template avoids this by using aria-hidden
                                      on the heading instead.
                                    #}
                                    <h4 class="visually-hidden">
                                        {{ 'Read more about ' ~ node.label | t }}
                                    </h4>

                                    {#
                                      IMAGE + FLAG REGION
                                      -------------------
                                      position-relative on this wrapper allows the flag
                                      overlay (position-absolute inside) to be positioned
                                      relative to the image area, not the entire card.
                                    #}
                                    <div class="position-relative">
                                        {# 
                                          PROMOTIONAL FLAG / BADGE
                                          ------------------------
                                          Only rendered when field_flag equals 'flag_on'.
                                          Renders a small colored banner in the top-left
                                          corner of the card image (e.g., "Giving Day",
                                          "Featured Story").

                                          DEV NOTE — FLAG CLASS ASSEMBLY
                                          This template uses a more advanced flag class
                                          assembly than Give Now. Rather than inline
                                          concatenation, it uses a filtered array:
                                            ['flag', 'py-2', node.field_flag_background.value ?: '']
                                            | filter(v => v)  → removes empty string if no bg value
                                            | join(' ') | trim → collapses to class string, trims whitespace

                                          This is slightly cleaner than Give Now's approach and
                                          avoids an extra trailing space when field_flag_background
                                          is empty. Consider back-porting this pattern to Give Now
                                          in a future consistency pass.

                                          Field explanations (same as Give Now):
                                            field_flag_background.value → background color class
                                            field_icon.value            → icon class string (Font Awesome)
                                            field_icon_size.value       → size modifier class
                                            field_icon_color.value      → inline hex/rgb color
                                            field_flag_title.value      → visible flag text

                                          aria-hidden="true" on the <i> icon suppresses it
                                          from screen readers (purely decorative).
                                        #}
                                        {% if node.field_flag.value == 'flag_on' %}
                                            {% set flag_classes = ['flag', 'py-2', node.field_flag_background.value ?: ''] | filter(v => v) %}
                                            <div class="position-absolute start-0">
                                                <div class="{{ flag_classes|join(' ')|trim }}"
                                                     style="width: max-content; display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 5px 10px; white-space: nowrap;">
                                                    {% if node.field_icon.value %}
                                                        <i class="{{ node.field_icon.value }} {{ node.field_icon_size.value }} px-1"
                                                           style="color: {{ node.field_icon_color.value }}"
                                                           aria-hidden="true"></i>
                                                    {% endif %}
                                                    {% if node.field_flag_title.value %}
                                                        <span class="flag-title">{{ node.field_flag_title.value }}</span>
                                                    {% endif %}
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        {% endif %}

                                        {# 
                                          CARD IMAGE
                                          ----------
                                          node.field_image.entity guard — same pattern as Give Now
                                          v2.2.0. Protects against a non-null field_image whose
                                          referenced file entity was deleted from the Media Library
                                          without being removed from the node. Without this guard,
                                          accessing .fileuri on a null entity causes a fatal error.

                                          image_style('lead_story') → applies the 'lead_story'
                                            Drupal image style derivative. Verify dimensions at
                                            /admin/config/media/image-styles. Update the style
                                            name here if it is ever renamed in the UI.

                                          alt_text fallback → 'Story image for {node.label}' when
                                            the editor left the alt field blank. This fallback is
                                            more descriptive than Give Now's 'Image for' prefix,
                                        #}
                                        {% if node.field_image.entity %}
                                            {% set image_url = node.field_image.entity.fileuri | image_style('lead_story') %}
                                            {% set alt_text = node.field_image.alt|trim is not empty ? node.field_image.alt : 'Story image for ' ~ node.label %}
                                            <div class="card-header mb-2">
                                                <img src="{{ image_url }}" alt="{{ alt_text }}" loading="lazy" class="img-fluid">
                                            </div>
                                        {% endif %}
                                    </div>{# END .position-relative (image + flag region) #}

                                    {#
                                      CARD TEXT CONTENT
                                      -----------------
                                      flex-grow-1 d-flex flex-column → this is what makes the
                                        CTA footer "stick" to the bottom of the card. flex-grow-1
                                        causes this content div to expand and fill all available
                                        vertical space, pushing the card-footer below it to the
                                        bottom of the <article>. Without this, the footer floats
                                        up to sit directly below the body text, breaking the
                                        aligned-bottom-edge visual across cards of different heights.
                                      px-3 pt-2 → horizontal padding and top breathing room
                                    #}
                                    <div class="lead-story-content px-3 pt-2 flex-grow-1 d-flex flex-column">

                                        {#
                                          DUAL HEADING STRATEGY — LAYER 2 (VISIBLE TITLE)
                                          ------------------------------------------------
                                          This <p> is the VISIBLE card title. It uses a <p>
                                          (paragraph) tag rather than a heading tag deliberately,
                                          because the <h4> above already handles the heading
                                          semantics for screen readers and the document outline.

                                          Using another heading tag here would double the heading
                                          in the AT reading order, which is why this is a <p>
                                          with heading-style typography classes (fs-4 fw-bold).

                                          id="{{ heading_id }}" → provides a DOM anchor for
                                            potential future aria-labelledby use (e.g., if the
                                            card pattern is ever refactored to expose the title
                                            as a separate interactive element).

                                          aria-hidden="true" → critical. Suppresses this visible
                                            title from the AT reading order because the hidden
                                            <h4> above already handles reading the title to AT
                                            users. Without this, screen readers announce the
                                            story title TWICE per card.

                                          Typography classes:
                                            fs-4  → Bootstrap font-size 4 (~1.25rem)
                                            fw-bold → bold weight
                                        #}
                                        <p id="{{ heading_id }}" class="fs-4 fw-bold" aria-hidden="true">
                                            {{ node.label }}
                                        </p>

                                        {#
                                          CARD BODY
                                          ---------
                                          node.body.value|raw → renders the Drupal body field
                                            with full HTML markup intact. The `|raw` filter
                                            bypasses Twig's autoescaping.

                                          ⚠ SECURITY NOTE: `|raw` is only safe here because
                                            Drupal's text format pipeline (CKEditor + configured
                                            text filters) already sanitized this content before
                                            storage. NEVER use `|raw` on unfiltered user input
                                            or fields not processed through a Drupal text format.
                                            If in doubt, use `{{ node.body.value }}` without |raw
                                            and inspect the output — Twig escaping will show you
                                            if the content contains unescaped markup.

                                          mb-2 → bottom margin before the CTA footer
                                        #}
                                        <div class="lead-story-body mb-2">
                                            {# |raw used with caution; respects Drupal filter configuration #}
                                            {{ node.body.value|raw }}
                                        </div>
                                    </div>{# END .lead-story-content #}

                                    {#
                                      CALL-TO-ACTION FOOTER BUTTON
                                      ----------------------------
                                      Only rendered when field_link.title is non-empty.
                                      Same guard as Give Now v2.2.0 — prevents an empty
                                      .card-footer div from appearing when no CTA label
                                      is configured, which would create unexpected whitespace
                                      at the bottom of the card.

                                      PATTERN NOTE: This is a <span>, NOT a <button> or <a>.
                                      It is intentionally non-interactive because the entire
                                      card is already wrapped in a clickable <a>. Nesting
                                      a <button> or <a> inside another <a> violates the HTML
                                      spec and causes AT to announce two separate interactive
                                      elements where there is only one action.

                                      aria-hidden="true" → hides this from screen readers.
                                        The CTA text ("Read the story", "Learn more") is
                                        redundant given the parent <a>'s aria-label. AT users
                                        do not need to hear it announced separately.

                                      Layout differences vs. Give Now CTA footer:
                                        - No mb-5 here (Give Now has mb-5 on the wrapper div)
                                        - w-100 text-start on the <span> — full-width button
                                          appearance, left-aligned text. Give Now omits these.
                                        - card-footer has mb-2 (vs. the more complex d-flex p-0
                                          mb-5 mx-3 pattern in Give Now)
                                        Consider aligning these in a future design system pass
                                        to reduce per-component variation.
                                    #}
                                    {% if node.field_link.title is not empty %}
                                        <div class="card-footer card-story mb-2">
                                          <span class="btn outline-btn-cu-bg-black text-decoration-none p-2 mt-3 w-100 text-start" aria-hidden="true">
                                            {{ node.field_link.title }}
                                          </span>
                                        </div>
                                    {% endif %}

                                </article>{# END article.lead-story-card #}
                            </a>{# END a.story-link (card anchor) #}
                        </div>{# END div[role="listitem"] (grid column) #}

                    {% endif %}{# END row._entity guard #}
                {% endfor %}{# END for row in view.result #}

            </div>{# END div[role="list"] .row (card grid) #}

            {# 
              GLOBAL CTA: Browse More Stories
              PLACEMENT: Should be positioned after the {% endfor %} loop of the story grid.
              ACCESSIBILITY: Uses clear, descriptive text for screen reader navigation.

              DEV NOTE — GLOBAL CTA FOOTER
              ------------------------------
              This "Browse More Stories" button lives OUTSIDE the loop and applies
              to the entire grid section, not to any individual card. It routes to
              /impact-stories which should be the full stories listing page.

              This element has NO equivalent in block--give-now.html.twig. It is
              unique to the Lead Story component's editorial intent.

              GA TRACKING ATTRIBUTES:
                data-ga-event         → event type (basic_block_link)
                data-ga-category      → GA category
                data-ga-action        → GA action label / event label
                data-ga-component-id  → hardcoded component ID for the GA layer.
                                        ⚠ This value ('block--node--basic-block--2016')
                                        is HARDCODED and tied to a specific node/block ID.
                                        If the block is cloned or recreated in a new
                                        Drupal environment, this ID will be stale. Consider
                                        replacing with {{ id }} or a dynamic value in a
                                        future refactor.

              LAYOUT CLASSES:
                card-footer d-flex justify-content-center → centered horizontal layout
                mb-5                                      → bottom margin before next section
                btn-cu-bg-gold                            → CUA theme gold button style.
                                                            Check _buttons.scss for definition.
                px-5 py-2 mt-4                            → generous horizontal padding,
                                                            vertical padding, top margin
            #}
            <div class="card-footer d-flex justify-content-center mb-5">
                <a href="/impact-stories" 
                class="card-link btn btn-cu-bg-gold text-decoration-none px-5 py-2 mt-4" 
                data-ga-event="basic_block_link" 
                data-ga-category="basic_block" 
                data-ga-action="Browse More Stories" 
                data-ga-component-id="block--node--basic-block--2016">
                    {{ 'Browse More Stories'|t }}
                </a>
            </div>

        </div>{# END .container-fluid (section wrapper) #}
    {% endif %}{# END view.result not empty #}
{% endif %}{# END content['#view'] not empty #}


